<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-1307] Stop converting user-defined runtime exceptions to NPEs</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-1307</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MongoTemplate has code like this in many places:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;} catch (RuntimeException ex) {&lt;br/&gt;
	throw exceptionTranslator.translateExceptionIfPossible(ex);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MongoExceptionTranslator, however, often does NOT return an exception. If it encounters an unknown exception it does this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;// If we get here, we have an exception that resulted from user code,&lt;br/&gt;
// rather than the persistence provider, so we return null to indicate&lt;br/&gt;
// that translation should not occur.&lt;br/&gt;
return null;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MongoTemplate then &quot;eats&quot; the original exception and throws a null-pointer exception instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MongoTemplate should throw the original exception if it gets null back from the exception translator.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
